The paper deals with triangulations of polygons, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of dynamic programming suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The investigation of the relationship between the dual diameter and the number of ears in a triangulation suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
